label: ISApu1
definition: IS4 family transposase originated in Aeromonas punctata.
definition source: https://isfinder.biotoul.fr/scripts/ficheIS.php?ident=1342

label: ISApu2
definition: IS4 family transposase originated in Aeromonas punctata. ISApu2 (ISUnCu5) is 78% aa similar to ISApu1
definition source: https://isfinder.biotoul.fr/scripts/ficheIS.php?ident=1342

label: ISKpn8
definition: IS3 family Insertion sequence originated from  K. pneumoniae
definition source: https://isfinder.biotoul.fr/scripts/ficheIS.php?ident=1342

label: ISKpn6
definition: IS1182 family transposase that originated from  K. pneumoniae. Insertion sequence found in Tn4401 that carries the KPC carbapenemase gene which has a role in KPC gene dissemination
definition source: Cuzon G, Naas T, Villegas MV, Correa A, Quinn JP, Nordmann P. Wide dissemination of Pseudomonas aeruginosa producing β-lactamase bla KPC-2 gene in Colombia. Antimicrobial agents and chemotherapy. 2011 Nov;55(11):5350-3.

label: Tn1721
definition: Tn1721 is a transposon, a mobile genetic element that can move within a genome. It may carry genes providing selective advantages or contribute to genetic diversity.
definition source: Rogowsky P, Schmitt R. Tn 1721-encoded resolvase: structure of the tnpR gene and its in vitro functions. Molecular and General Genetics MGG. 1985 Jun;200(1):176-81.

label: RepA
definition: RepA typically refers to a replication initiator protein found in plasmids. These proteins are essential for initiating plasmid DNA replication within bacterial cells.
definition source: Rozwandowicz, M., Brouwer, M.S.M., Fischer, J., Wagenaar, J.A., Gonzalez-Zorn, B., Guerra, B., Mevius, D.J. and Hordijk, J., 2018. Plasmids carrying antimicrobial resistance genes in Enterobacteriaceae. Journal of Antimicrobial Chemotherapy, 73(5), pp.1121-1137.

label: Inc13
definition: A plasmid replicon type commonly associated with beta-lactam resistance genes
definition source: Shintani M, Sanchez ZK, Kimbara K. Genomics of microbial plasmids: classification and identification based on replication and transfer systems and host taxonomy. Frontiers in microbiology. 2015 Mar 31;6:242.

label: IncA/C2
definition: A plasmid replicon type commonly associated with beta-lactam resistance genes
definition source: Papagiannitsis CC, Kutilova I, Medvecky M, Hrabak J, Dolejska M. Characterization of the complete nucleotide sequences of IncA/C2 plasmids carrying In809-like integrons from Enterobacteriaceae isolates of wildlife origin. Antimicrobial agents and chemotherapy. 2017 Sep;61(9):10-128.

label: IncFIA
definition: A plasmid replicon type commonly associated with beta-lactam resistance genes

label: IncFIB
definition: A plasmid replicon type commonly associated with beta-lactam resistance genes

label: IncFII
definition: A plasmid replicon type commonly associated with beta-lactam resistance genes

label: IncFIIA
definition: A plasmid replicon type commonly associated with beta-lactam resistance genes

label: IncN
definition: A plasmid replicon type commonly associated with beta-lactam resistance genes

label: IncP
definition: A plasmid replicon type commonly associated with beta-lactam resistance genes

label: IncR
definition: A plasmid replicon type commonly associated with beta-lactam resistance genes

label: IncX4
definition: A plasmid replicon type commonly associated with beta-lactam resistance genes

label: IncX5
definition: A plasmid replicon type commonly associated with beta-lactam resistance genes

label: IncH
definition: A plasmid replicon type commonly associated with beta-lactam resistance genes

label: ColRNAI
definition: ColRNAI plasmids are present in Gram-Negative bacteria that play a role in conjugal transfer to receipients
definition source: Sugita K, Aoki K, Komori K, Nagasawa T, Ishii Y, Iwata S, Tateda K. Molecular analysis of bla KPC-2-harboring plasmids: Tn 4401a interplasmid transposition and Tn 4401a-carrying ColRNAI plasmid mobilization from Klebsiella pneumoniae to Citrobacter europaeus and Morganella morganii in a single patient. Msphere. 2021 Dec 22;6(6):e00850-21.

label: MOBF
definition: relaxases of the MOBF family are large proteins that consist of two domains: an N-terminal relaxase domain in which there are two catalytically active tyrosines and a C-terminal helicase domain
definition source: Garcillán-Barcia MP, Francia MV, de La Cruz F. The diversity of conjugative relaxases and its application in plasmid classification. FEMS microbiology reviews. 2009 May 1;33(3):657-87.

label: MOBP
definition: MOBP is a cluster of actively evolving relaxases, with several distinguishable clades
definition source: Garcillán-Barcia MP, Francia MV, de La Cruz F. The diversity of conjugative relaxases and its application in plasmid classification. FEMS microbiology reviews. 2009 May 1;33(3):657-87.

label: MOBV
definition: MOBV family relaxases are constantly evolving and play a huge role in mobile genetic elements transfer
definition source: Garcillán-Barcia MP, Francia MV, de La Cruz F. The diversity of conjugative relaxases and its application in plasmid classification. FEMS microbiology reviews. 2009 May 1;33(3):657-87.

label: MOBH
definition: MOBH family relaxases are present almost exclusively in conjugative plasmids
definition source: Garcillán-Barcia MP, Francia MV, de La Cruz F. The diversity of conjugative relaxases and its application in plasmid classification. FEMS microbiology reviews. 2009 May 1;33(3):657-87.

label: MOBQ
definition: MOBQ family relaxases are highly divergent
definition source: Garcillán-Barcia MP, Francia MV, de La Cruz F. The diversity of conjugative relaxases and its application in plasmid classification. FEMS microbiology reviews. 2009 May 1;33(3):657-87.

label: MPF_F
definition: putative T4SS's assosiated with congugative pilus for vir system
definition source: Smillie C, Garcillán-Barcia MP, Francia MV, Rocha EP, de la Cruz F. Mobility of plasmids. Microbiology and Molecular Biology Reviews. 2010 Sep;74(3):434-52.

label: MPF_T
definition: putative T4SS's assosiated with congugative pilus for F system
definition source: Smillie C, Garcillán-Barcia MP, Francia MV, Rocha EP, de la Cruz F. Mobility of plasmids. Microbiology and Molecular Biology Reviews. 2010 Sep;74(3):434-52.

label: MPF_I
definition: putative T4SS's assosiated with congugative pilus for R64 system
definition source: Smillie C, Garcillán-Barcia MP, Francia MV, Rocha EP, de la Cruz F. Mobility of plasmids. Microbiology and Molecular Biology Reviews. 2010 Sep;74(3):434-52.

label: MPF_G
definition: putative T4SS's assosiated with congugative pilus for ICEHIN1056 for Haemophilusinfluenzae genome island-like system
definition source: Smillie C, Garcillán-Barcia MP, Francia MV, Rocha EP, de la Cruz F. Mobility of plasmids. Microbiology and Molecular Biology Reviews. 2010 Sep;74(3):434-52.

label: istB
definition: istB-istA gene products have a role in the transposition of IS21
definition source: Reimmann C, Moore R, Little S, Savioz A, Willetts NS, Haas D. Genetic structure, function and regulation of the transposable element IS 21. Molecular and General Genetics MGG. 1989 Feb;215:416-24.

label: IS21
definition: Insertion sequence that is closely related to IS116 family, involved in mobility of cfr gene plasmids
definition source: Kehrenberg C, Aarestrup FM, Schwarz S. IS 21-558 insertion sequences are involved in the mobility of the multiresistance gene cfr. Antimicrobial agents and chemotherapy. 2007 Feb;51(2):483-7.

label: Tn5403
definition: Tn5403 transposon belongs to Tn3 family like transposons are associated with blaCTX-M-55 antibiotics resistance genes
definition source: Zheng Z, Li R, Ye L, Wai-chi Chan E, Xia X, Chen S. Genetic Characterization of bla CTX–M–55-Bearing Plasmids Harbored by Food-Borne Cephalosporin-Resistant Vibrio parahaemolyticus Strains in China. Frontiers in Microbiology. 2019 Jun 18;10:1338.

label: KikA
definition: A region on IncN group of plasmids
definition source: Hengen PN, Denicourt D, Iyer VN. Isolation and characterization of kikA, a region on IncN group plasmids that determines killing of Klebsiella oxytoca. Journal of bacteriology. 1992 May;174(9):3070-7.

label: Plasmid inheritance protein
definition: proteins that confer selective advantages to bacteria such as antibiotic or virulence factors
definition source: Hiraga S. Mechanisms of stable plasmid inheritance. Advances in biophysics. 1986 Jan 1;21:91-103.

label: IS6100
definition: IS6100 may play an important role in the establishment of carbazole-degrading pathway,
definition source: Gai Z, Wang X, Liu X, Tai C, Tang H, He X, Wu G, Deng Z, Xu P. The genes coding for the conversion of carbazole to catechol are flanked by IS 6100 elements in Sphingomonas sp. strain XLDN2-5. PLoS One. 2010 Apr 2;5(4):e10018.

label: ISKpn19
definition: ISKpn19 element is are associated with Tn2 family transposons that play a role in dissemination of fluroquinolone and beta-lactam resistant genes
definition source: Zhong YX, Liu WT, Yuan PB, Yang L, Xu Z, Chen DQ. Characterization of the bla VEB-3 bearing IncC plasmid and bla KPC-2 bearing IncFII plasmid in a type IE CRISPR-Cas system harboring Klebsiella oxytoca stain.

label: DNA-invertase
definition: DNA invertase is an enzyme that mediates site-specific DNA inversions. These inversions typically occur at adjacent regions of DNA and can flip the orientation of DNA segments.
definition source: Zhou Z, Xiang Y, Tong A, Lu Y. Simple and efficient method to purify DNA–protein conjugates and its sensing applications. Analytical chemistry. 2014 Apr 15;86(8):3869-75.

label: trpR
definition: TrpR repressor protein represses the transcription of mtr operon
definition source: Zhao Z, Chen S, Wu D, Wu J, Chen J. Effect of gene knockouts of L-tryptophan uptake system on the production of L-tryptophan in Escherichia coli. Process Biochemistry. 2012 Feb 1;47(2):340-4.

label: trpA
definition: tryptophan synthase from Chlamydia trachomatis
definition source: Michalska K, Wellington S, Maltseva N, Jedrzejczak R, Selem‐Mojica N, Rosas‐Becerra LR, Barona‐Gómez F, Hung DT, Joachimiak A. Catalytically impaired TrpA subunit of tryptophan synthase from Chlamydia trachomatis is an allosteric regulator of TrpB. Protein Science. 2021 Sep;30(9):1904-18.

label: ISKpn7
definition: IS1182 family transposase that originated from  K. pneumoniae. Insertion sequence found in Tn4401 that carries the KPC carbapenemase gene which has a role in KPC gene dissemination
definition source: Naas T, Cuzon G, Truong HV, Nordmann P. Role of IS Kpn7 and deletions in bla KPC gene expression. Antimicrobial agents and chemotherapy. 2012 Sep;56(9):4753-9.

label: ISEc29
definition: ISEc29 contains tnpMut which is mutator transposase
definition source: Yousfi K, Touati A, Lefebvre B, Fournier É, Côté JC, Soualhine H, Walker M, Bougdour D, Tremblay C, Bekal S. A novel plasmid, pSx1, harboring a new Tn 1696 derivative from extensively drug-resistant Shewanella xiamenensis encoding OXA-416. Microbial Drug Resistance. 2017 Jun 1;23(4):429-36.

label: ISKpn21
definition: IsKpn21 is a ISNCY element associted with mcr and beta-lactam genes
definition source: Yuan Q, Xia P, Xiong L, Xie L, Lv S, Sun F, Feng W. First report of coexistence of blaKPC-2-, blaNDM-1-and mcr-9-carrying plasmids in a clinical carbapenem-resistant Enterobacter hormaechei isolate. Frontiers in Microbiology. 2023 Mar 23;14:1153366.

label: ISBcen27
definition: Associated with colistin resistance
definition source: Peng Z, Dottorini T, Hu Y, Li M, Yan S, Fanning S, Baker M, Xu J, Li F. Comparative genomic analysis of the foodborne pathogen Burkholderia gladioli pv. cocovenenans harboring a bongkrekic acid biosynthesis gene cluster. Frontiers in Microbiology. 2021 May 17;12:628538.

label: ISAba125
definition: ISAba125 insertion sequence associated with NDM transposons

label: ISKpn14
definition: IS elements associated in mediating colistin resistance

label: ISKra4
definition: DDE transposase

label: IS630
definition: IS630/Tc1/mariner DNA transposon family transposase
definition source: Puzakov MV, Puzakova LV, Cheresiz SV. An analysis of IS630/Tc1/mariner transposons in the genome of a Pacific oyster, Crassostrea gigas. Journal of Molecular Evolution. 2018 Oct;86(8):566-80.

label: IS1380
definition: IS1380 family transposase contain metronidazole-resistant elements
definition source: Veloo AC, Chlebowicz M, Winter HL, Bathoorn D, Rossen JW. Three metronidazole-resistant Prevotella bivia strains harbour a mobile element, encoding a novel nim gene, nimK, and an efflux small MDR transporter. Journal of Antimicrobial Chemotherapy. 2018 Oct 1;73(10):2687-90.

label: IS30
definition: Family of insertion sequences that have role in colistin resistance
definition source: Snesrud E, He S, Chandler M, Dekker JP, Hickman AB, McGann P, Dyda F. A model for transposition of the colistin resistance gene mcr-1 by IS Apl1. Antimicrobial agents and chemotherapy. 2016 Nov;60(11):6973-6.

label: IS1595
definition: Superfamily of Insertion Sequences associated with IS6/IS26 family of insertion sequences
definition source: Harmer CJ, Hall RM. An analysis of the IS6/IS26 family of insertion sequences: is it a single family?. Microbial genomics. 2019 Sep;5(9).

label: IS110
definition: IS110 family members are associated with GES carbapenemase gene dissipations
definition source: Botelho J, Grosso F, Sousa C, Peixe L. Characterization of a new genetic environment associated with GES-6 carbapenemase from a Pseudomonas aeruginosa isolate belonging to the high-risk clone ST235. Journal of Antimicrobial Chemotherapy. 2015 Feb 1;70(2):615-7.

label: IS5
definition: IS5 family insertion sequences

label: ISL3
definition: ISL3-like insertion sequences derived from Pseudomonas stutzeri associated with various beta-lactam antibiotic resistance dissemination
